    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d9961058_2ca81361",
        "filename": "android/kernel/kernel_utils.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 66,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-07-16T07:11:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: Use a static const array instead, as in:\n\n  static const char kVersionStringPrefix[] \u003d \"Linux version \";\n  static const size_t kVersionStringPrefixLen \u003d sizeof(kVersionStringPrefix) - 1U;\n\nThis avoids a static C++ constructor on the line below.",
      "revId": "7ce5442271c52c6f5dd1184103703dc19d3bbdfc",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d9961058_6cb21bd3",
        "filename": "android/kernel/kernel_utils.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 76,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-07-16T07:11:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oops: if |size| is 0, this will overwrite the buffer with |srcLen| bytes. You probably want something different, as in:\n\n  size_t srcLen \u003d strlen(src);\n  if (size \u003e 0) {\n    size_t copyLen \u003d std::min(srcLen, size - 1U);\n    memcpy(dst, src, copyLen);\n    dst[copyLen] \u003d 0;\n  }\n  return srcLen;",
      "revId": "7ce5442271c52c6f5dd1184103703dc19d3bbdfc",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "198d0845_4efb9357",
        "filename": "android/kernel/kernel_utils.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 92,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-07-16T07:11:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It looks like this code assumes that the version string prefix is at the start of |versionString|, but strstr() will return non-NULL if it appears later in the string.\n\nI\u0027d suggest either use strncmp() instead of strstr() to enforce the \"version string must be at start of string\" contract, or increment the result of strstr() instead. Probably the former is better.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 92,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 92,
        "endChar": 17
      },
      "revId": "7ce5442271c52c6f5dd1184103703dc19d3bbdfc",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d9961058_4cad5f70",
        "filename": "android/kernel/kernel_utils.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 115,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-07-16T07:11:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: avoid using sprintf() here to keep security auditors happy :-)\n\nMore generally, you can use LogString() to perform formatted output in log statements (this should avoid allocating temporary variables when logs are disabled). As in:\n\n  KERNEL_LOG \u003c\u003c android::base::LogString(\"Kernel version hex 0x%06x\", temp);",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 115,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 115,
        "endChar": 11
      },
      "revId": "7ce5442271c52c6f5dd1184103703dc19d3bbdfc",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
