      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-07-16T07:11:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Off-topic: Technically speaking, the prefix to use also depends on the target architecture, i.e. for ARM64, which is not currently supported by the Android emulator, this must be \u0027ttyAMA\u0027 with kernel 3.10.\n\nDon\u0027t bother about this for now, because ARM64 will happen through a QEMU executable for now, but we will have to modify the API at some point.",
      "revId": "7ce5442271c52c6f5dd1184103703dc19d3bbdfc",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
